caption: AVOID RESTAURANT WEEK!!!! Generally speaking this is a pretty decent place.  Good food and good prices.  The restaurant menu is $39 for a $20 pasta dish a sample sized appetizer and half sizes dessert.  Net true value about $25 so approx $14 over priced if you just ordered from menu.
I go back every time just for their ravioli

Il Porcellino is by far one of my favorite restaurants to visit when in the city.  My husband and I always have an amazing experience.  We sat at the bar tonight and had the pleasure of having Jose serve us.  Wonderful atmosphere, amazing food and outstanding service!  Highly recommend to anyone looking for a cozy place with delicious food!
Amazing Italian food!

IL Porcellino is a must!  We recently had a small family dinner here, and we couldn’t have been happier. From the moment I called to set up a reservation, to the moment we concluded our dinner, we have been accommodated like kings and queens. The attention to detail in setting up the reservation: food sensitivities, table set up, preordering the appetizers, ensuring that we had our private area for our family to mingle,(just a few to mention) was exquisite.  The food was delicious, small piece of advice here, I think we went a little heavy on the appetizers, which were so good, that by the time we had to order entrees we were a little too full.  The space is beautifully decorated, lighting was perfect to instill a romantic, intimate and relaxing atmosphere  coupled with Frank Sinatra’s songs, it makes on forget about all the stresses of the current times we live in.  While respecting all the city guidelines for indoor dinning, it is safe to say that for a few hours that we spent here, we were able to relax and enjoy each other’s company much like pre-Covid times.  If you are planning a small intimate event, this is the place to be!
Awesome all around.

This place was amazing. The food and service was great. We ended up here because we were avoided at a steakhouse restaurant. We were at within 10 mins. Service was great and awesome recommendations. Food was cooked perfectly. I would definitely recommend.
Good food and great wait staff and bartenders. Quality hospitality!

First time out since Feb. 2020 and this place had a rhythm. They have made plexiglass look clean and appealing. You need to make reservations, either standard seating, outside or at the bar. Temp check once reservation has been confirmed. Hand sanitizer stations. Mask must be worn at all times unless eating or drinking, especially when staff approach you. Bathrooms (yes, I said plural, 3 to be exact and 2 are spacious) the signs in the bathroom are fun facts when it comes to hand wash time. Ok! Now the food is amazing! Recommend the Tuscan bread for an app. You can taste quality in everything. Drinks are clean and strong (esp cocktails). Recommend the Jimmy 2 times or an old fashion which was prepared PERFECTLY. Anything u order is going to taste great. Allergies are reported to the chef. N95s are worn by all staff. My server was Axel and he was just the BEST! They really made me feel anxiety free during this rough time.

Amazing service, amazing food, great experience ❤️ Julio our server was the nicest and explained the menu perfectly! It was our anniversary and we couldn’t agree more that we were not wrong with the place we chose! Thanks so much
Jose was an amazing waiter - very helpful and kind, and the food was incredible! We recommend the ravioli and the tiramisu!
Great place for a dinner,great music. The Menu was okay(not many options actually)  But this is great place with a great food.

Added Feb 20, 2021. Popped in for a Negroni and ordered the app of grilled calamari in a spicy sauce! So perfect! I wanted something light sans carbs. Ate half and leftovers next day even better. Cannot recommend this place enough. Last review: Succulent pasta. Yes, I know this is not common for pasta... but their pairing with delicious sauces and succulent proteins is remarkable. Today, had some ravioli. Last time something with ribs. Time before, same thing. Also good beverages. Wine list or specialty cocktails.
So many great things on the menu! Cavatelli or alla vodka or basic fettuccini alfredo are all amazing. And the happy hour deals are a nice bonus.
Throughly enjoyed dinner here. While the service was exceptionally slow, our server was polite and respectful. The ambiance is amazing. Food was delicious. I am excited to return.

Very nice atmosphere, our waiter Jake was great and very knowledgeable about the options. Got a good amount a food that was delicous at a fair price. The garlic bread loaf is a definite! Definably will be back
Ok food
Chic restaurant with a cute vibe. Loved the chianti bottles on the ceiling as decor with the photos all over the wall! MUST have their cacio e pepe, it's to die for, some of the best in the city

Please don’t eat here. The reviews are a send off. If you want a cute atmosphere for drinks it’s cute for that but the food was trash.. could make better pasta at home then here. Not authentic Italian food .. I swear they used some Barilla boxed pasta for my meal
Really tasty and high-quality food
Great

Amazinggggg!! Great option for covid outdoor dining. My husband and I usually always have to take food to go bc we can never finish. But here we cleaned our plates!! The steak was perfect and the spicy shrimp scampi was delicious!! Apps and dessert are a must!

We made a reservation for 4 people two weeks ago, when outdoor dining was the only option. Since indoor dining opened on the day of our reservation, we expected to be seated indoors instead. However, that was not the case. No attempt was made to accommodate us indoors, even though 2 indoor tables opened up while we were talking with the concierge. We left and ate at Havana nearby, which was much more accommodating.
It was delicious

Probably the best COVID-outdoor dining accommodations available in the city. Support this business! You literally eat dinner in your own private, decorated, *heated* greenhouse. Not to mention the food was cooked absolutely perfectly and was so flavorful! The drinks are great (and half the price during happy hour) and the service was awesome! I cannot wait to go back! 10/10 recommend!

This was my first first. I'm going with four stars, but that's with some leniency on service. The greeting staff was friendly and accommodating. I was the first of our party to arrive, so I had a Manhattan at the bar. Nice atmosphere, but a little more Manhattan and quite a bit less block artisan ice would be just fine with me. We were seated promptly. The acoustics is quite noisy when the place is hopping - which is was. Our server was friendly and offered good advice when asked. Caution - be aware of the incredibly aggressive bus staff. Hang onto your plates if you're not finished. There's efficiency and then there's rudeness, and this bordered on the latter.
Food was amazing.  Jose the Bartender has a true talent for mixology.  Sampled 2 apps, 3 entrees and 2 desserts and nothing disappointed.
A fav spot for tasty Italian food. I give this place double thumbs up. Quick and friendly service. Prices that are reasonable.

I don't have enough words for this place. It's just amazing. Food is authentic and very much like what we had in Florence, Italy. Every thing from Apps, pasta and my personal favorite - chicken piccata were incredibly delicious. Hands down one of the best italian restaurant in the city.
Outstanding place for Italian food. It was so savory. Prices are decent. Food is similar to a cafe in Indianapolis I loved.

I took my wife here for our one year anniversary and it was nothing short of my expectations. The atmosphere was chique and romantic. The freaking meatballs and lasagna were heavenly! The bartender mixed drinks like it was New Years Eve! This is a true authentic Italian restaurant, not an Olive Garden or Maggiannos. Read my virtual lips: TRUE AUTHENTIC ITALIAN CUISINE. Now get over there and have a damn meatball.
Delicious pastas, must try the garlic bread.

I order pick up food was good except for the calamari. Looking at the pics I thought I would get something fried instead I got something in a tomato sauce that tastes absolutely awful. It's fishy, it's burnt it just tastes horrific. I want my $15 back for an appetizer that went to the trash. You also didn't include silverware so imagine eating at the hotel turned into a mission. The beer to go is okay sort of like a Budweiser. The alfredo and chicken parm were good just not worth the price.
Delicious!! We ordered 4 different things from menu and none of them disappointed!!

Porcellino is a nice and decent italian restaurant in the heart of downtown chicago!  Delicious food, nice presentstion. Overall its a good place to enjoy italian flavors. We had : garlic bread (loved it) Chicken marsala.  Definitely recommend :)  During covid they have very few tables open for dining, so reservation is required. Also very limited parking nearby since its on the hubbard.

A fav of mine in Chicago!! Everything I’ve ever gotten here is down right delicious!! My recommendations: burrata and Brussels for apps, rigatoni alla vodka for main course, and donuts or tiramisu for dessert. But you legit can’t go wrong. A MUST try in Chicago!!

Great atmosphere and service was second to none. Food was delicious and original. We would definitely  come back!

I am so disappointed about this place. After trying for two days to get a reservation I finally got one by calling them for Monday Nov 09 2020 at 8:15 pm. When I got there with my BF the lady who work there as a host asked me where we came from and she rejected us because we came from Florida and because of that we were not allow to eat in but the real true about this is that at that time there wasn’t any table available for us and because we are Hispanic they want us to be out of their restaurant. Place pick another place we find another Italian restaurant two blocks away and it was delicious and we didn’t have any problem getting in.
GREAT FOOD GREAT STAFF
Favorite italian spot. Cacio e Pepe with sausage was delicious. Garlic Loaf was also phenomenal. Great service and atmosphere.
Cheese bread and roasted chicken penne were fabulous! Will definitely be back!
Best Italian restaurant I’ve been to. Their spicy scampi spaghetti is excellent. I always have to stop by and have a meal when I’m in Chicago.
By far, this is the best Italian ever tried in US.
This is my favorite Italian restaurant in Chicago!
italian food at this location - delicious. Got there about three, it wasn't crowded. This place has a cool atmosphere.

- Get a text saying our table inside is ready at 8:30 - Arrive at 8:40, table should be ready in under 10 mins - at 9:15 they say no inside tables will be available for another half hour, we agree to sit outside (45 degrees out) - Order at 9:30, by 10:30 our entrees are not out and we leave. I think they forgot about our table since we were the only ones outside.  I appreciate that the manager didn't charge us, but I would rather pay be warm and eat food than sit and wait in the cold.  The appetizers were good, so I'm guessing this place has good food if you can get your reservation honored
Amazing pasta, atmosphere was great and friendly service
Great all around the lasagna is amazing

Very nice restaurant. Keep in mind in cooler weather it’s completely open so you may get some cigarette smoke from the side walk, and here the nose of cars, motorcycles, and sirens.  I’d still recommend their food though. Delicious.
This restaurant has a great atmosphere
Food and drinks were delicious! Our server who was also the bartender was amazing. Cute place for a date or ladies night! Will return!
Delicious meal! The pasta is homemade and fantastic. The orecchiette is very fresh and light tasting.
Amazing! Fabulous food, wonderful service.  Can't wait to return.

Ok spot for quality Italian food. entered near eleven, it wasn't packed. really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, i'll be back. prices are appropriate for the quality. i can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.
Great service.

My food sensors go buck wild anytime someone even mentions Il Porcellino - Something as simple as a caprese salad comes to LIFE here. So happy I have this place  a few blocks away. It truly is the best Italian in the area. *PEACE, LUV, MEATBALLS*

I can’t tell you how much I love this place. If the owners are reading *please* put the tortellini back on the menu. Amazing service and I’d argue best red sauce in downtown Chicago. Never have trouble getting a table and look forward to every meal I get to enjoy here.
Been here multiple times whenever I crave Italian food and this place never disappoints. Always start with the cheese bread and pretty much everything I’ve tried here is amazing!

Had our first meal in Chicago here and WOW!  Did not disappoint.  Cheese bread was out of this world.  Lasagna was the best I have ever had.  My vegetarian wife LOVED her pesto penne pasta.  Fantastic meal and service.
Horrible food
Get the lasagna and the cheese bread

I had there fettuccine alfredo and their appetizer of cheese bread while I was staying in Chicago. The flavor of their fettuccine alfredo was outstanding.  The bacon pieces on the top I would have to say is the best bacon I've ever had.  I also would like to give a big shout out to the staff they are very friendly.

I had this delivered for dinner tonight and it was absolutely FABULOUS!! They really did a great job with packaging everything so that it kept well and looked really nice and sophisticated. Everything was labeled WITH refrigeration and reheating instructions. The food was quick, great quality, and delicious. The personal thank you note from the manager was sweet and thoughtful. We went big - it was Friday date night - so we went with the cheesy bread appetizer, spaghetti and meatballs, and steak. You have GOT to try the cheesy bread. It could just be the bread lover in me, but it’s the best thing/comfort food I’ve had in WEEKS. Entrees were just as good!

Take out during COVID. Not as warm and fresh as dine-in of course, but still can see how great the taste is and will definitely come back once restaurants are open again. P.S. they said they don’t provide tableware for takeout so make sure you clarify if you need tableware.

Seriously disappointed. Got quarantine takeout and was severely underwhelmed. It was boxed pasta and Ragu levels of tasty. Looking at my plate, I'm pretty sure I'm actually eating Barilla. I could have slapped together an equally unimpressive dinner for my partner for $7 instead of $70. The tiramisu was outstanding, meriting a second star. Maybe they should stick to baked goods.
Nice ambience. Good food and prices.
Beautiful place, great main dish, fantastic dessert.

Have had the opportunity to travel and see the original Porcellino in Florence but dining at Il Porcellino in Chicago is a treat. Ask for the special, the baked burrata lasagna ;-) and Julio for great service! The ambiance is great!
Great food and very nice ambiance.

Fantastic Italian restaurant. Has a nostalgic Italian feel, nice music selections, and most importantly one of the best tasting menus in the city. You can't go wrong with any selection. Be sure to come hungry, as well, because they do not skimp on portion sizes. Tuscan cheese bread appetizer is a must-try as well. Fantastic experience all around. Will return.

Amazing Italian restaurant in River North! And unlike most of the places in Chicago, you can find a pretty good meal here after 10pm given they are open pretty late. The crispy hurrays was definitely the perfect starter. Special shout out to their pasta: the tomato sauce and the 3 meat ragu were delicious! We are definitely coming back for more.
I'll give props to the atmosphere, but the food was pretty disappointing. Definitely not worth the price tag
Great negronis
Great for happy hour.

First time at this restaurant. We were a party of five, we waited forever to get our food we all got lasagna because we heard it was the best at this place. Some of us got a cold lasagna I got what looked like the leftover scraps of lasagna. I don't recommend it. I won't be back!
I loved the atmosphere, ambience, the service, and the  food had a good taste, However once our food came it was lukewarm.

Last week was our first time we came to that place. But It is no doubt not the last time. We enjoyed the evening very much with the excellent service, with the first-rate cooking and wine and with the comfortable pay. We will definitely visit there again.
I love this place. A real authentic American/Italian. Delicious menu, fabulous service in a cozy bustling setting. A must visit!!

Had a marvelous time! From the moment we arrived, service was exceptional. The gentleman that took us to our table was welcoming and friendly. Mario was our server - he took great care of us and made excellent recommendations. Shout out to the male bartender as well - he made me the best espresso martini I have ever had! We enjoyed the burrata special, the cacio e pepe, and the tiramisu. So good!
Loved the garlic bread and staff would go just for that. My pasta was supposed to have various seafood.  It just had shrimp and pasta noodles were huge.
OMG this place is amazing. The service is great and the atmosphere is beautiful. Food is delicious and to die for. Anytime I’m in Chicago I will have to try it again!!!!
Amazing food, great ambience! Stuffed mushrooms, burrata and Tuscan cheese is a must try!
Great casual Italian food.  Service and atmosphere was also excellent.
The Food was Delicious.. me & my friend enjoyed it...

I think it should be rated 3 dollar signs instead of 2 because it is pretty pricey. Aside from that, I have absolutely nothing bad to say. I make tasty homemade sauce, but mine has NOTHING on there's. I don't know what they do, but there is so much flavor in there sauce. Even the chicken (chicken parmesan) had all this flavor and was very tender. I was stuffed full, but still finished my meal because i couldn't stop eating it. I don't live in Chicago and that makes me sad, because I won't be able to eat here all the time. Even the vinaigrette they use on the Italian salad was amazing. To top in off, the service is above board. Very attentive and nice. Could not recommend this place more. Do yourself a favor and eat here.

I tried out Il Porcellino for Restaurant Week as I heard great things. As far as I could tell, the RW menu was different from their regular menu. We got the Burrata Bruschetta, Green Chopped Salad, Fruitti Di Mare, and Tiramisu cake from the RW menu and also ordered the  Fettuccine Alfredo which I thought was a good balance between two people.  The Bruschetta was easily the worst dish. The bread was over-toasted, and difficult to eat which really took away from the flavors. It also seemed like the dish was pre-made as it came out pretty quick so a little disappointed with this one.  The chopped salad was pretty good, although it was a bit spicy from the pepperoncini seeds. I do enjoy spice, but just a warning in case. The  Frutti Di Mare and Fettuccine Alfredo were good, and the Tiramisu was great, and perfect size.  Overall, it was a good experience. Service was good, food was a bit forgettable, but overall Il Porcellino provides a cool ambiance and it's a nice date night spot.

I will give this place 5 stars for service. The staff was very attentive and came on a regular basis to ask if we needed anything. The food was not out of this world but it was good and good portions. The bread was delicious especially that they pour the olive oil. I would come back for a drink and some appetizers but I do wish they out more thought into their meals.
We had an amazing experience here! The service was top notch and 36 hour pork chop was delicious.
An elegant take on Italian-American classics. Delicious.
Jon and Ashway behind the bar are delightful!

This place is absolutely amazing!! Just left here and I already can't wait to go back. Everything is top knotch every time I've been here. I came down from Minnesota just to eat here, no joke! It is that good!! Seriously, the LASAGNA!!!! 🤤😭🤤😭🤤😭🤤😭 Love it!!!!
Food was good and so was the service.
Great food..very reasonable prices..

The atmosphere is great. Such a nice Italian restaurant. I got the fettuccini Alfredo and added chicken to it and it was delicious! My favorite part was the free bread they bring out with the olive oil. It was so good we had our waitress bring 3 rounds of it. Would definitely come back!
The highlight of the evening was Mario The service by Mario was EXCELLENT The food was great We are definitely in Italy Fresh and tasty product We absolu you love this place ❤️
Drinks, food and service were all first class. Vibe is fun. Menu is always changing and fresh. Don't miss a chance to add this to your favorites list. Great place!
Good atmosphere (music, decor, friendly and intelligent staff), beer list is small but well-chosen. Can't review food or wine because I just had beers and small bar sandwich. Try this place.
Fun drinks

Great cocktails and appetizers. Not rushed. Dinner was fantastic, get the tortellini. Chris is an amazing server who gave the perfect suggestions. Cute place inside, not too fancy but not too casual. Will absolutely be returning.
Such a wonderful experience. Everything from ambiance and service to food and wine was amazing. We spent over 2 hours at the restaurant. Well priced for the quality and location.
I don’t know how it could’ve been better.

We came on New Year's Eve, and the staff was super awesome. The cocktails are to die for, and I don't say this lightly, but it was the best meal of my life. Maybe that makes me sheltered, but damn the food is good.
Very good Italian-American.
Lovely atmosphere. Food is good and reasonable. Staff was friendly, although there was an issue when we went to pay the bill and it took ten minutes for us to close out.
Food is really good and the family meal is the best value for your buck

(Translated by Google) Lovely restaurant, excellent service, super friendly waitresses and outstanding at all times. Exquisite dishes, I recommend it.  (Original) Encantador restaurante, excelente servicio, camareras súper amigables y pendientes en todo momento. Platos exquisitos, lo recomiendo.
Great food and outstanding service. Our group had a fantastic time celebrating our holiday party
Excellent food and service. My only complaint was that the family style menu portions, which were shared between four people, were a little on the small side.

What a delightful evening!  Attentive service, remarkable food (pasta so delicate I had to look close to be sure it was really there!), decadent desserts.  Interesting wine list.  It's a busy place, deservedly so, plan ahead and make a reservation...and do go!

Great staff and food. Would totally recommend bringing the family in for some legit Italian cuisine. It’s low lit and nicely decorated. Would recommend making a reservation even on weekdays since it gets busy later in the evening. The grilled calamari was my favorite.
The staff was friendly and knowledgeable, the atmosphere was lively and warm, the drinks were delectable, and the food was delicious. Recommend a reservation for weekends.
Great food and service.
Very nice surprise
We went in a group and ordered 2 bottles of Chianti. Had a great time, enjoyed the ambience and appetizers. The service is fast. This is a expensive place so look out if you are on budget.
From valet service to the dessert, just wonderful! I highly recommend the calamari!

Two people in our party had the carbonara and they just could not finish it due to it being way too salty. They did offer dessert on the house which was a nice gesture. The other entrees were good but not amazing.
Great pasta. Try the crispy brussel sprouts (even if you don't like brussel sprouts these are amazing). Make sure you get reservations as it fills up quick.
An Italian jewel in the windy city. The Lasagna and garlic bread are not to miss!

Delicious food and outstanding service! Eric was a fantastic server that seemed to go above and beyond with recommendations and menu knowledge. We will definitely be back the next time we visit Chicago.
Great place. Good food.

We visited here the night before Thanksgiving. The place was hopping! Our server Christin was great! The pace was right, and the food was delicious! We all enjoyed the Tuscan cheese bread. The salads were fresh and delicious. The ravioli dish was yummy as was the chicken parmigiana. I must say I’d go back just for the donut dessert! OMG. 5 little warm donuts with 2 different sauces were the best!! Put this place on your list Chicago visitors.... you’ll be happy you did!
We were very disappointed with our meal. The food was mediocre. We felt like we were at an Italian chain, not an authentic restaurant experience. The service was also poor.
Sit at the bar. You will get dinner and a show. The bartenders know how to show off making drinks.

Everything was perfect, and just what we wanted to experience with our family. Perfect decor and embiance. Service was great, food was great, wine selection was great, and the atmosphere was perfect. Made a great ending to our trip to Chicago. I'd classify this as fine dining, but the prices are very reasonable, and worth every penny.
Great food, great service, loved the atmosphere our waiter was great recommended the tortellini al forno it was delicious... thanks for the recommendation!
Low quality main dish
Excellent service and food
(Translated by Google) Excellent, delicious, highly recommended.  (Original) Excelente, delicioso, muy recomendable.
Great pasta & very friendly people
Cacio e Pepe was so good! Will come back!
Amazing place with amazing dessert. We ordered the tiramisu. Do not miss it if you ever visit the place. The best one I've had
Probably the best Tiramisu cake I've had in ages. Pastas are flavourful and antipasti selections are a great way to start the meal.
Solid happy hour, good Negroni
Nice place, the red wine is good. Fot the dessert I prefer the double chocolate cake than tiramisu...

Came here on Friday evening and it wasn't too busy. I wish I could remember the name of our waiter but he was fantastic. I swear the water in my glass didn't drop by an inch before he would come to check on us and refill. We were a little pressed for time but our food came out quickly and was delicious. Portion sizes were generous and the friendliness of the staff was unmatched.
The service was over the top! Excellent food as well!

The food was above average, but the service was really weird. They stopped at our table every couple of minutes and kept trying to take our plates away. It was clear that they wanted us out asap. It was uncomfortable. I will not be back.
Was at the bar and bartender Jose helped me out the whole step of the way from the wine down to the menu! Awesome person awesome place!
This could be the best restaurant I have been to in the same category. Feel good menu, clean open-space design, great service. Simple yet rich dishes. We need more places like this.

Impromptu dinner with my company planned 6 hours in advance for a group of 60. Jerry and her team were amazing. I don't know if she handles the hiring or not..whoever does is doing terrific. Amazing food, amazing atmosphere, amazing place to celebrate life. Thank you from the team at Midwest Express Clinic
Great food and service

Fantastic restaurant. Cool laid back dimly lit environment with great Sinatra style music. The garlic bread is so good and the chicken parmigiana was unreal. Peter was our server and was friendly, fast, professional and made great recommendations.

Will have to come back to Chicago just to eat here again.  We fought hard to get a table on a Saturday night  here after poor prior planning on our part. I am glad we did!  It was raining so hard all day so it seemed like all the tourists were just hunkering inside wherever they could find a good warm, dry spot. There were no reservations available but we were told we could wait for a table for an hour and 45 minutes... Never having eaten here before, we weren't sure it'd be quite worth that long of a wait...  We thought we would check open table one more time before committing to another establishment and lo and behold...we got a table for 10 minutes from now!! We basically dashed out of the bar we were taking shelter in and sat in a Lyft for about 7blocks of gridlocked traffic (which hurt my soul...but we got fully drenched walking a couple blocks to the bar we were at).  We got to Il Porcellino about 5minutes late and were seated right away at a high top by the bar.  We got a caprese salad which was terrific! 5/5! The waitress said there was no vinegar but there was a mystery acid that gave it just the right amount of zing. Delicious!  I got the sausage orichette and it was very good! 8/10. Came here for dinner with some friends and this place did not disappoint. Our waitress was amazing and so was the service overall. We ordered the whole loaf bread, stuffed mushrooms, calamari and the green chopped salad as appetizers. Don't sleep on the bread here. It was extra fluffy inside and with the combination of warm butter and garlic it was delicious. If you salad do yourself a favor and order the green chopped salad. This is no mediocre salad as they pack on the kale, cheese, nuts and great vinaigrette dressing.  As for the entrees, we ordered the tortellini al forno, orecchiette, pappardelle alla porcellino and the gnocchi bolognese. You can tell everything here is really fresh. As the pastas had great texture. I enjoyed the gnocchi the most because they cooked it really well the seasoning in the bolognese was delicious. The orecchiette and pappardelle were very good as well.  My friends and I really enjoyed our dining experience here as well. We left stuffed. The ambience here is great as they have indoor ceiling light features. We saw large parties start coming in around 6 PM. They have great seating to accommodate medium to large size parties. Highly recommend this place if you want awesome quality pasta and Italian food overall.

Also, a lot of Italian places like to go for a "classic" or "sheik contemporary" look and it always fails. The lighting and design of the place is super chill and welcoming.
